Sammie Okposo has deleted his Instagram and Twitter account after pulling down a post, where he admitted to cheating on his wife. Recall that the gospel artist had tendered a public apology for having an affair with a USA-based lady identified as African Doll. Top 8 Celebrity Power Couples in Nigerian Entertainment Industry Actress Iyabo Ojo shares rough experience as single mum Following his post, the lady he had an affair and allegedly impregnated had an interview and the video has since gone viral on social media. In the video, the lady disclosed how they met and began their relationship. Since his post on Tuesday, the gospel singer has been trending on social media. Further checks have shown that Sammie Okposo has deleted his verified Twitter  and Instagram accounts, as the page shows that the account doesn’t exist His Twitter account reads, “This account doesn’t exist,  try searching for another.” Also, Instagram reads “Sorry this page isn’t available, the link you followed may be broken or the page may have been removed. Go back to Instagram.”